```rust
pub fn is_rule_enabled(&self, key: &str) -> bool {
    self.inner.get(key).cloned().flatten().unwrap_or(false)
}
```

If the config has `key` in `inner` with value `None`, then `get` returns `Some(None)`, `.cloned()` gives `Some(None)`, `.flatten()` gives `None`, and `.unwrap_or(false)` gives `false`. So ALL rules would be disabled.

But then in `organized_lints` and `lint`, the wasm code calls `fill_with_curated()` BEFORE linting, which resets the config:

