The `.unwrap()` here is on `as_word()` which returns `Option<&Option<DictWordMetadata>>`. For a `Word(None)`, this returns `Some(None)`. For any other TokenKind, this returns `None`, and `.unwrap()` would PANIC.

But the `expr` only matches `Word` variants, so this should be fine.

