The "No snapshot!" error means the snap files were generated but they don't match (because the test expects them to EXIST). Actually wait, looking at the `tag_file` function:

```rust
fn tag_file(...) -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    ...
    let has_snapshot = snapshot_file.exists();
    if has_snapshot {
        let snapshot = std::fs::read_to_string(snapshot_file)?;
        if tagged == snapshot {
            return Ok(());
        }
    }

    // write snapshot
    std::fs::write(snapshot_file, tagged)?;

    Err(if has_snapshot {
        "Snapshot mismatches!".into()
    } else {
        "No snapshot!".into()
    })
}
```

So when `has_snapshot` is false (after deletion), it writes the snapshot but returns an error "No snapshot!". The snapshots are now generated. Let me run the test again:

